README.md:3:A local Windows-friendly property search dashboard for Australian coastal properties.
README.md:7:The app has 330 curated property records using direct listing pages, with 311 currently visible active 
listings. Sold, under-offer, under-contract, withdrawn, off-market, or leased records are hidden automatically. The 
app does not scrape portal search pages in the browser.
README.md:9:When opened through `Start Property X Factors.cmd`, the local server starts an automatic suburb sweep 
every 5 minutes. The sweep follows the selected red-line mainland coast only: starting at Adelaide, west across SA/WA 
to Geraldton, then looping to Mackay and following the east/south coast back through NSW, VIC, and SA. Near cities, 
the route breaks the coast into every direct beach-access suburb, including smaller Adelaide suburbs such as Glenelg 
North, Somerton Park, and Hove. Standard suburbs get up to 2 minutes; suburbs within about 2 hours of a major city get 
10 minutes. It adds verified direct listing records as they are found, up to 10 per run. The `Search now` button 
triggers the next suburb in the same sweep immediately, and the page reloads when a search finishes.
README.md:11:Use `SA search` to run a focused manual search from Semaphore through Cape Jervis, preferring listings 
within 2 hours of Adelaide.
README.md:15:Newly discovered properties are highlighted gold in the comparison table and marked with a star until you 
click the row/card or open the exact listing.
README.md:27:- Beachfront properties
README.md:28:- Beachfront properties with no road in front
README.md:30:- Properties within 1 hour of a major city
README.md:31:- Larger land/block sizes
README.md:35:Use the `Favourite` button on any property card to save it. The `Favourites` view in the header shows 
only favourited active properties, and `Export favourites` downloads that saved list.
README.md:39:Major Australian property portals usually do not allow unrestricted scraping. This app is built for 
compliant workflows: agent exports, your own listing notes, saved listing URLs, or a future licensed API feed.



